data.title: FUBAR Season 2: Check out what is latest development about filming, cast and more
data.meta_description: Netflix announces the start of filming for FUBAR Season 2, starring Arnold Schwarzenegger and Monica Barbaro. The series follows CIA operatives Luke and Emma Brunner. New cast member Carrie-Anne Moss joins the show. A release date is yet to be confirmed.
data.text:
Synopsis

Netflix announces the start of filming for FUBAR Season 2, starring Arnold Schwarzenegger and Monica Barbaro. The series follows CIA operatives Luke and Emma Brunner. New cast member Carrie-Anne Moss joins the show. A release date is yet to be confirmed.

Netflix has announced that the second season of FUBAR has started filming. Arnold Schwarzenegger and Monica Barbaro return to continue the story of Luke and Emma Brunner. The series, created by Nick Santora, follows the comedic adventures of the Brunners as they navigate their lives as CIA operatives. A new video released by Netflix features Schwarzenegger celebrating the production start with an action figure of his character.

Plot and Characters

In the first season, Luke Brunner (Arnold Schwarzenegger) is introduced as a secret CIA operative. He takes pride in his work but is unaware that his daughter Emma (Monica Barbaro) is also an operative. This leads to chaos as they try to hide their occupations from each other. Eventually, they must work together on a delicate mission. Despite being skilled agents, Luke still treats Emma as his little girl, creating a dynamic that adds to the series' humor.

Returning Cast

The first season's cast includes Milan Carter, Gabriel Luna, and Fortune Feimster. Carter, known for his television roles, takes on his biggest role with FUBAR. Luna is recognized for his roles in The Last of Us and Terminator: Dark Fate. Guest performances by Adam Pally and Tom Arnold also added to the comedic elements of the show.

New Addition

Netflix has announced that Carrie-Anne Moss will join the main cast for the second season. Moss will be seen in The Acolyte, a Star Wars series about the Jedi Order, before appearing in FUBAR. Her role in the new episodes is expected to bring a fresh dynamic to the Brunners' latest assignment.

Production and Release

The final stages of pre-production are complete, and filming for the new episodes has begun. A release date for the second season has not yet been announced.

FAQs:

When will 'FUBAR' Season 2 be released?

Netflix has not announced a release date yet for 'FUBAR' Season 2, but filming has begun.

Who is joining the cast for 'FUBAR' Season 2?

Carrie-Anne Moss will join the main cast of 'FUBAR' Season 2, adding a new dynamic to the series.
